  "prompt": "What is our body made up of cells or atoms?",
  "response": "The human body is made up of both cells and atoms. \n\nCells are the basic structural and functional units of life. Different types of cells form tissues, organs, and ultimately systems that make up the human body. \n\nAtoms, on the other hand, are the fundamental units of matter and make up the molecules within cells. These molecules include water, proteins, lipids, carbohydrates, and nucleic acids, which are essential for the structure and function of cells.\n\nIn summary, the human body is composed of cells, which in turn are made up of atoms organized into molecules.",
